cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MM

This paper deals with the impact of packet skipping and network coding on the timely communication of messages through a network element. It involves the study of queueing systems, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with the optimization of network performance, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of thresholding policies and network coding also involves control systems, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the study of goodput improvement, which is related to cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper involves the modeling of network coding operations, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
